  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "Roll out the pastry dough to a thickness of 1/8 inch.",
    "Cut out 6-8 squares of pastry, depending on desired size.",
    "Place a tablespoon of feta cheese in the center of each square.",
    "Brush the edges of the pastry with melted butter.",
    "Fold the pastry in half to form a triangle, pressing edges to seal.",
    "Brush the tops of the borek with remaining butter.",
    "Bake for 20-25 minutes, or until golden brown.",
    "Serve warm, garnished with chopped parsley if desired."
